{{Infobox journal | title = Communication Education | cover = | editor = Melanie Booth-Butterfield | discipline = [[Communication]] | formernames = | abbreviation = Commun. Educ. | publisher = [[Taylor & Francis]] on behalf of the [[National Communication Association]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1952-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.tandf.co.uk/journals/titles/03634523.asp | link1 = http://www.natcom.org/index.asp?bid=238 | link1-name = Journal page at Association's website | link2 = http://www.tandfonline.com/toc/rced20/current | link2-name = Online access | link3 = http://www.tandfonline.com/loi/rced20 | link3-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = 2076115 | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 0363-4523 | eISSN = 1479-5795 }} '''''Communication Education''''' is a quarterly [[academic journal]] covering speech and communication on college campuses. It is published by [[Taylor & Francis]] on behalf of the [[National Communication Association]].
